Pop a #saucepan{} on medium-high heat. Add the @Korma Sauce{225%g} and bring to the boil.

Stir in the @Diced British Chicken Breast{260%g}, then lower the heat and cover with a #lid{}. Simmer, ~{10-12%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash hands and utensils after handling raw meat. Cook so there's no pink in the middle.

When the curry is almost ready, halve the @Plain Naans{2} widthways, then toast in your #toaster{} until golden.

Squeeze the @Steamed Basmati Rice{1} pouch to separate the grains. Tear a strip approx 2cm along the top. Microwave for 800W: ~{2%minutes} / 900W: ~{1%min 30secs} / 1000W: ~{1%minute}.

Meanwhile, stir the @Peas{120%g} through the curry and simmer, ~{1-2%minutes}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Share the rice between your #bowls{}.

Top with your curry and a dollop of @Greek Style Natural Yoghurt{75%g}.

Drizzle over the @Mango Chutney{40%g} and sprinkle with the @Toasted Flaked Almonds{15%g}.

Serve the naans alongside. Enjoy!